	"metadata": {
		"title": "USN-2536-1 -- libXfont vulnerabilities",
		"description": "Ilja van Sprundel, Alan Coopersmith, and William Robinet discovered that libXfont incorrectly handled malformed bdf fonts. A local attacker could use this issue to cause libXfont to crash, or possibly execute arbitrary code in order to gain privileges.  Update Instructions:  Run `sudo pro fix USN-2536-1` to fix the vulnerability. The problem can be corrected by updating your system to the following package versions:  libxfont1 - 1:1.4.7-1ubuntu0.2 libxfont-dev - 1:1.4.7-1ubuntu0.2 libxfont1-udeb - 1:1.4.7-1ubuntu0.2 No subscription required",
